HEADWORD: Cackler
<hw>Cac"kler</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>A fowl
that cackles.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>One who prattles, or tells tales; a
tattler.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cackling</ent>⟦br⟧
